	"description": "How do you protect yourself online without having to remember a million\nimpossible passwords? \n\nThis is an (actually) easy to implement guide, which is the digital equivalent\nof locking your house when you leave. \n\nTaking these steps won’t make you hack-proof (just as locking your house won’t\nmake your house burglar-proof) but it will make you much safer online. It also\nwon’t make your digital life any harder than carrying keys makes your day-to-day\nlife. \n\nIf you&#x27;re convinced that this is too m",
