	"keywords": "Cybersecurity, Infosec, Information Security, Ssl, tls",
	"description": "The SSL and TLS protocols are frequently attacked. And understanding past\nattacks can inform your knowledge as a defender and help you secure current\nsystems. It can also help you predict the direction of future attacks.\n\nSo here&#x27;s a summary of some of the most famous attacks targeting these\nprotocols:\n\nBrowser Exploit Against SSL/TLS (BEAST):\nBEAST (disclosed in 2011) allowed a man-in-the-middle attacker to discover\nencrypted information from an SSL/TLS session. It impacted SSL 3.0 and TLS 1.0.",
