	"keywords": "Information Security, Infosec, Cybersecurity",
	"description": "What is a SIM swap?\nSIM swapping is when a hacker convinces your cell phone carrier to switch your\nphone number to a different SIM - one that they own. \n\nThis is a relatively normal thing for a retail employee to do, which means that\nsomeone asking for a swap doesn’t raise red flags. (Imagine that you bought a\ndifferent phone and now needed to switch where your cell service was so you\ncould continue receiving texts/calls on your new device).\n\nIt doesn’t require a hacker to have any technical kno",
