	"keywords": "Cybersecurity, Information Security, Infosec, Application Security",
	"description": "Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks aim to take an organization or\nservice offline and originate from multiple, distributed hosts. \n\nThe difficult part of defending against DDoS attacks is that the hosts are\ndistributed – if it were a single host or small group, you could easily block\nthe traffic with a firewall rule. \n\nThere are many different types of DDoS attacks, but we can broadly group them\ninto three categories – volumetric, protocol, and application attacks. Let&#x27;s\nlook at each o",
